From 6b5900d77916d369dc57bd14c062fd264916a842 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: fi3 <email@email.com>
Date: Wed, 10 Jun 2026 16:32:28 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 1/4] ADD selected-agent backend command routing to keep slash
 input out of chat prompts

Slash-prefixed selected-agent chat input needs provider-native command handling so commands like /status and /fork resume the active backend thread without being injected as ordinary prompts. The backend trait keeps existing providers source-compatible through a default unsupported-command response, while Codex overrides the path with a command resume invocation.
---
 docs/architecture.md  |  12 +++
 src/agent_runtime.rs  |  21 ++++-
 src/cli.rs            |  46 +++++++++++
 src/codex.rs          | 181 ++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++------------
 src/workspace.rs      |   8 +-
 tests/terminal_app.rs |  33 +++++++-
 tests/workspace.rs    |  59 ++++++++++++++
 7 files changed, 303 insertions(+), 57 deletions(-)

diff --git a/docs/architecture.md b/docs/architecture.md
index b6ee24f..7c7e713 100644
--- a/docs/architecture.md
+++ b/docs/architecture.md
@@ -95,8 +95,13 @@ port when the requested address is unavailable.
 
 - `AgentBackend::launch` starts an agent session from an `AgentLaunch`.
 - `AgentBackend::send` sends a prompt to an existing agent session.
+- `AgentBackend::execute_command` sends a provider-native command to an existing agent session.
+  Providers that do not support this path use the default implementation, which returns an
+  unsupported-command agent message without treating the input as a normal chat prompt.
 - `AgentBackend::launch_streaming` and `AgentBackend::send_streaming` provide real-time output to a
   sink of `AgentStreamEvent` values. Their default implementations call the non-streaming methods.
+- `AgentBackend::execute_command_streaming` provides real-time output for provider-native commands.
+  Its default implementation calls `execute_command`.
 - `AgentBackend::shutdown_handle` returns an `AgentShutdownHandle` for terminating active provider
   processes.
 - `AgentStreamEvent` carries status text, streamed agent messages, and streamed errors.
@@ -127,6 +132,10 @@ public lifecycle extension is required before external child processes can parti
   `codex exec` and `codex exec resume` calls. Launch invocations include the injected
   `PromptPolicy`; resumed invocations for known sessions pass only the follow-up message because the
   Codex thread already contains the launch-time policy and repository instructions.
+- `CodexBackend::build_command_invocation` constructs selected-agent slash command resumes as
+  `codex exec resume --json <thread-id> <command>` without prompt stdin, so Codex handles commands
+  such as `/status` and `/fork user-2` through its backend command path rather than as ordinary
+  follow-up chat text.
 - `CodexBackend::record_launch_reply`, `record_launch_output`, and `session` maintain in-memory
   session state.
 - `CodexBackend` parses Codex `--json` event lines from stdout to capture `thread.started`
@@ -166,6 +175,9 @@ The primary public methods are:
 
 `CommandChat` uses the active `AgentProfile` when launching user agents, reviewers, and linearizers.
 Workflow code must not hard-code `AgentKind::Codex` when the active profile supplies the provider.
+When UI-driven selected-agent chat text starts with a non-empty slash command token, such as
+`/status`, `CommandChat` routes it through `AgentBackend::execute_command_streaming` instead of the
+ordinary send/resume prompt path. Inputs such as `/` or `/ status` remain ordinary chat text.
 
 ## UI-Neutral Controller
 
